      "post_content": "@robox: They shouldn't have the \"old\" wording at all. That would functionally change how the card works. The card always let you cast auras as though they had flash, it's just that auras weren't always called auras. I can't say that changing this from working with 700+ auras - which will only get more and more cards every set, some of which are removal - to less than 100 enchantment creatures would be a good thing.  \n  \nCertainly aura removal like [Pacifism](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pacifism) and [Journey to Nowhere](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Journey to Nowhere) would benefit from being instant speed, but also effects like [Aspect of Mongoose](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Aspect of Mongoose) that could essentially counter spells after drawing out the removal, which casting on your turn wouldn't do. I'm sure there are plenty of other awesome things that could be done with instant-speed auras. There are 700+ of them, after all, so go digging through Gatherer and have some fun planning a [Bruna, Light of Alabaster](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bruna, Light of Alabaster) deck.",
      "posted_by": "sarroth",
